<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-7261] @Lazy should work in combination with @Delegate</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-7261</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;@Delegate uses the delegate field directly but that won&apos;t have been set if also using @Lazy. We might eventually allow this to be customizable, e.g. with a flag like &apos;direct = false&apos; or &apos;forceDirect&apos; or &apos;useDelegateField&apos;, but for now we should at least just fix the common case.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Expected behavior:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;Foo {
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;private&lt;/span&gt; @Delegate @Lazy ArrayList list = [&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;bar&apos;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;baz&apos;&lt;/span&gt;]
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// fragile: $list is an internal implementation detail that may change
&lt;/span&gt;  def getInternalDelegate() { $list }
}

def f = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Foo()
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;assert&lt;/span&gt; f.internalDelegate == &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;assert&lt;/span&gt; f.size() == 2
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;assert&lt;/span&gt; f.internalDelegate == [&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;bar&apos;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;baz&apos;&lt;/span&gt;]
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
